# StockWay UI — no tick thrash

`renderAll` runs on **every market tick**. Full `innerHTML` rewrites destroy hover/focus and cause flash/blink/stutter.

**Seen in production:** Estates Residences glow thrash at 10x — fingerprint included live **cash/NW**, so ticks remounted the bento and killed CSS `:hover`.

## Required pattern for any interactive panel

Estates, Staff/HR, Vault, Collection, Achievements, Finance, Dashboard widgets, **and any new feature surface**:

1. **Structure fingerprint / skip** — rebuild DOM only when ownership, selection, navigation, or catalog identity changes.
2. **Patch live values** with `textContent` / class toggles / attribute updates — never remount a card grid to refresh numbers.
3. **One-shot enter animations** only on real navigation; strip the class after `animationend`.
4. Prefer **border/opacity** hover — not transform + image-scale + box-shadow + backdrop-filter on large tiles.
5. Avoid continuous CSS **filter/blur** animations on large surfaces.
6. Bind clicks with **delegation once** (or only after a real remount) — do not re-`onclick=` every tick.

## Fingerprint anti-patterns (will reintroduce Estates stutter)

**Do NOT** put these in a structure key / snap string:

- Live `portfolio.cash`, quote prices, or fine-grained net worth
- Per-tick progress meters, clocks, or “last updated” timestamps
- Anything that changes more than a few times per second while the player hovers

**Do** put: owned ids, selected id, active tab/category, ledger open, day index, spent totals that only change on buy/sell actions.

Patch Ready/Locked/affordability **in place** when cash/NW moves (`patchEstatesLive`, `patchRosterLive`, `setHtmlIfChanged`).

